# Coverage Decide Verify

{% include "runtime/partial/stage_verification_contract.md.j2" %}

For coverage_decide, verify that every positive CoveredProductType is backed by explicit table applicability evidence from its selected chart_path in the verified table artifacts. Do not infer coverage from weak substring matches alone. chart_path and evidence_path_list are artifact references, not product-type coverage evidence. Verify that coverage_decide read every referenced chart_path and relevant evidence_path_list artifact before using those artifacts for coverage. Positive coverage may be backed by loaded chart content, loaded evidence content, applicability_description, or chart description. Verification must fail when positive coverage depends only on path strings. Identifier-only fields are supporting context, not coverage evidence. source_url, source_title, size_group_key, and country_code_list identify the table and source authority, but they must not be the only basis for a positive product-type coverage decision.

Verify that table-scoped fields are not used for product-level gaps. CoveredProductType.reason may explain only one positive product-type coverage decision from one verified chart_path; it must not be the location that explains why one requested product type remains uncovered.
